Raw dev notes -- Building a Messaging Monitor with AI Digests (March 2026)

A side project of mine grew a lot this month. What started as a simple group message
monitor turned into an information pipeline: message aggregation, daily AI-generated
digests, newsletter ingestion, and a lot of operational hardening.

Major features built:
- Daily AI digest via Gemini: summarizes all monitored groups into a concise report
- Separate digest pipeline for specialized content categories
- Email newsletter ingestion via IMAP polling
- Article filtering pipeline: LLM filter + content fetch + compression
- Auto-forward digest to relevant groups with randomized timing
- Schedule-aware processing (respects off-hours/holidays)
- Reminder system with persistence across restarts
- Push notifications for critical alerts (session loss, failures)

Operational hardening:
- Docker watchdog with health checks and crash forensics
- Escalating recovery (container restart -> service restart)
- Non-blocking startup with catch-up for missed messages
- Deduplication: cleaned up thousands of duplicate records
- Security: bound all service ports to localhost only

Struggles:
- Some message groups have permanently broken API responses -- no upstream fix available
- Docker daemon crashes on Windows required auto-detection and restart
- Sleep prevention on Windows was harder than expected
- Catch-up after downtime needed careful checkpoint logic to avoid duplicates

The system now runs 24/7, monitoring dozens of groups, filtering articles, ingesting
newsletters, and sending daily summaries. It's become my personal information hub.

Next: Move to a dedicated low-power device, add admin API, better embeddings.
